### Understanding Basic Code

```python
# File -> main.py
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI() # app  Convention     !

@app.get("/") # Decorator = Magic Function Apply -> root()

# @instanceName.httpMethod/method("Path")  

def root(): # root = login, get_user   !
    return {"message": "Hello World"} # Dict  API = JSON!
```

 Path Operation Function Create   !! 

```python
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI()

@app.get("/")

def root(): 
    return {"message": "Welcome to the API!!"}

@app.get("/yourpath")
def any_name_you_want():
    return {"key:": "Value"} # Save And Reload !!
```

### Path Operation Function Order 

```python
from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI()

#   get("/"), 1st Times  Occur    !!  

@app.get("/usersinfo") # get("/") -> No
def user_info():
    return{
	    "firstName":"Mahtabul",
	    "lastName":"Shourav"
    }
    
@app.get("/")
def root(): 
    return {"msg2": "This is msg 2!"} # Order1 get("/") -> Yes

@app.get("/")
def root():
    return {"msg1": "This is msg 1!"} # Order2 get("/") -> No 
```
